3. Bridge protocol — Worker C ↔ Worker A WebSocket
Wire format: text frames carrying JSON. Each envelope has {type, id, …}. id is a UUIDv4 generated by Worker A for outbound requests and echoed by Worker C in every reply.

3.1 Inbound envelopes (Worker A → Worker C)
Copy{
  "type": "sse_request",
  "id": "req_<uuid>",
  "method": "POST",
  "path": "/api/organizations/{org}/chat_conversations/{conv}/completion",
  "headers": {"Content-Type":"application/json","Accept":"text/event-stream"},
  "body": {"prompt":"…","model":"claude-opus-4-7", …},
  "timeout_ms": 120000,
  "stream": true
}
Other inbound types: cancel, ping, set_mutation_mode, set_system_prompt, discover_org, create_conversation, get_status.

3.2 Outbound envelopes (Worker C → Worker A)
Copy{"type":"sse_chunk", "id":"req_<uuid>", "data":"event: content_block_delta\ndata: {…}\n\n"}
{"type":"sse_complete", "id":"req_<uuid>", "status":200, "headers":{…}}
{"type":"sse_error", "id":"req_<uuid>", "status":429, "error":{"type":"rate_limit_error","message":"…"}}
{"type":"pong"}
{"type":"org_info", "org_uuid":"…", "account_uuid":"…", "user_email":"…"}
{"type":"convo_created", "conv_uuid":"…", "for_request":"req_<uuid>"}
3.3 Refusal rules (enforced inside Worker C)
Worker C drops any inbound envelope whose:

headers.Cookie is set (refuses cookie injection).
path starts with anything in the blocked-host list (api.anthropic.com, console.anthropic.com, platform.claude.com).
path is not under /api/, /edge-api/, or /v1/code/.
body contains a top-level system field that exceeds 64 KB (mutation cap).
Worker C never reads document.cookie or invokes chrome.cookies.*. The only cookie source is the browser itself, supplied automatically through credentials: 'include'.

