9. WebSocket reconnection — exponential backoff with jitter
Worker C's WS client uses decorrelated jitter (AWS pattern):

Copy// base = 1000ms, cap = 30000ms
let attempt = 0;
function nextDelay() {
  const base = 1000, cap = 30000;
  const exp = Math.min(cap, base * 2 ** attempt);
  const jitter = Math.random() * exp;
  return Math.min(cap, base + jitter);
}
This prevents synchronized reconnect storms when Worker A restarts WS jittered backoff. Reset attempt to 0 after a successful pong. App-level pings every 25 s, pong tolerance 35 s.

10. Trusted Types and document-start
The userscript registers at @run-at document-start so the fetch override lands before the page's React bootstrap captures window.fetch. If the site's CSP blocks the script registration with Trusted-Types-Report-Only, the script falls back to document-idle and re-patches in a MutationObserver on <head> to catch a late TT policy install. The Trusted-Types policy created by the script (trustedTypes.createPolicy('cfc-bridge', {createHTML, createScript, createScriptURL})) is used only if the diagnostics panel needs to inject debug DOM — never for fetch/XHR bodies, because those aren't TT sinks Tampermonkey TT issue 1334.

